    "body": "Issue seems to be resolved on the latest stable Lodestar release (v1.8.0)\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce**\r\n\r\nFetch finalized checkpoint\r\n\r\n```sh\r\ncurl https://lodestar-goerli.chainsafe.io/eth/v1/beacon/states/finalized/finality_checkpoints | jq \".data.finalized.root\" | tr -d '\"'\r\n```\r\n\r\nRun light client\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n./lodestar lightclient --network goerli --beaconApiUrl https://lodestar-goerli.chainsafe.io --checkpointRoot 0x56dab04d46366b3054d50e5854b04ed5b5f0d5d4539e9162430dc0cc558af743 --logLevel debug\r\n```\r\n\r\nObserve optimistic and finality header updates\r\n\r\n```sh\r\nJun-13 08:10:43.366[]                debug: Started tracking the head\r\nJun-13 08:10:50.212[]                debug: Updated state.optimisticHeader slot=5844053\r\nJun-13 08:11:02.814[]                debug: Updated state.optimisticHeader slot=5844054\r\n...\r\nJun-13 08:13:14.177[]                debug: Updated state.optimisticHeader slot=5844065\r\nJun-13 08:13:14.180[]                debug: Updated state.finalizedHeader slot=5844000\r\n```\r\n\r\nAlso confirmed on the beacon node side, it only subscribes once, thanks to https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/5151.\r\n\r\n\r\nClosing issue for now, @Daniel-K-Ivanov feel free to reopen if you are still facing this problem on latest version.",
